        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 5:27PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Vale, or 9 miles south of Paris, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Camden, Vale, Springville, Routon, Big Sandy, Mansfield,
Haigler Ridge, Manleyville, Old Springville, Van Dyke, Mixie, Spring
Creek, Crews Store, and Ephesus.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
